    {
      "id": "f4dc50fa03f1e7820e1444090571f4d4",
      "url": "https://pvp-ai.russell-harper.com",
      "title": "LLM plays an 8-bit Commander X16 game using structured \"smart senses\"",
      "content": "<p>I connected the ChatGPT API (model gpt-4o) to an 8-bit shoot-'em-up game, PvP-AI, running on a Commander X16 emulator.<p>Instead of pixels or audio, the model receives structured text summaries, what I\u2019m calling \"smart senses\", based on the game's existing touch and EMF-style inputs.<p>The LLM maintains notes between turns, develops strategies across games, and even discovers an exploit in the built-in AI's behavior.<p>Write-up, technical details, and three sequential gameplay recordings: <a href=\"https://pvp-ai.russell-harper.com/#v3\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://pvp-ai.russell-harper.com/#v3</a></p>\n<hr />\n<p>Comments URL: <a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47689550\">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47689550</a></p>\n<p>Points: 7</p>\n<p># Comments: 0</p>",
      "author": "russellharper",
      "published_date": "2026-04-08T12:56:58+00:00",
      "source": "Hacker News",
      "status": "pending",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [],
      "word_count": 83,
      "reading_time": 1,
      "created_at": "2026-04-08T14:53:02.765062+00:00",
